    "longBusinessSummary": "Lam Dong Minerals and Building Materials Joint Stock Company manufactures and trades in construction materials in Vietnam. It operates through Business in Building Materials, Contracting and Mining; Production and Business of Refractory Ceramics; Brick Production; Kaolin Mining and Processing; Stone Mining and Production of Reinforced Concrete; and Production and Sale of Solar Energy segments. The company offers ready-mixed concrete, such as commercial and flexible; tunnel bricks; construction stone for use in civil and industrial construction, and transportation; Kaolin DQK for use in the production of refractory materials and making bones in the ceramic industry; and Kaolin HTK for the civil ceramic industry, ceramic tiles, granite, and fillers in water paint. It also provides bentonite products for construction, fertilizer, chemical, and environmental industries; refractory materials, including Styrofoam and refractory bricks, refractory ceramic pipe products, unshaped refractory ceramic products, carbuasilic calcining pillars, and chamotte DQK-SM products; and Samot powders, post-fired products, and crushed stone. In addition, the company is involved in the construction and installation of civil, industrial, transportation, irrigation, and water supply projects, as well as land levelling; freight transportation by road; mining, processing, and trading of minerals; import and export activities; mining and exploitation of stone, sand, gravel, and clay; manufacture of concrete and products from cement, plaster, and gypsum; and construction of houses. Further, it engages in the wholesale of other installation equipment in construction; warehousing and storage of goods; trading in real estate; cargo handling; motor vehicle rental; afforestation, forest care, and nursery of forest trees; and generation of solar power. Lam Dong Minerals and Building Materials Joint Stock Company was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Da Lat, Vietnam.",
